      <h1>Director's Loan Account and S455 tax: what every limited company director should know</h1>
      <p class="canonical"><strong>Question:</strong> How is S455 tax calculated on a director's loan and how can it be avoided or reclaimed?</p>
      <p class="excerpt"><strong>Excerpt:</strong> The S455 tax rate for loans made on or after 6 April 2026 is 35.75%. For loans made between 6 April 2022 and 5 April 2026, the rate is 33.75%. The deadline for repayment to avoid S455 tax is 9 months and 1 day after…</p>
