<ol><li><strong>&quot;VAT deferred adjustment meaning HMRC&quot;</strong>: This addresses one of the client's specific questions.</li></ol>
<ul><li>Deferred VAT often relates to the VAT deferral scheme during COVID-19. If all deferred VAT wasn't paid, HMRC might query it.</li><li>Could also refer to adjustments for bad debt relief, partial exemption, or capital goods scheme.</li></ul>
<ol><li><strong>&quot;changing VAT number process HMRC&quot;</strong>: This addresses another client question.</li></ol>
<ul><li>Generally, a VAT number doesn't change unless the legal entity changes (e.g., sole trader incorporates).</li><li>If a business structure changes, a new registration might be needed, and the old one cancelled. VAT1 and VAT2 are for new registrations and transfers of going concerns.</li></ul>
<ol><li><strong>&quot;HMRC VAT letter for sole trader&quot;</strong>: This should confirm that the process is largely the same as for limited companies, but the underlying business structure is different.</li><li><strong>&quot;HMRC VAT discrepancies common causes&quot;</strong>: This will add detail to the &quot;Discrepancies and Penalties&quot; section.</li></ol>
<ul><li>Errors in data entry.</li><li>Incorrect application of VAT rules (e.g., exempt vs. zero-rated).</li><li>Timing differences (e.g., invoice date vs. payment date).</li><li>Mistakes in calculating partial exemption.</li><li>Bad debt relief not correctly applied.</li></ul>
